Prueba de conocimientos

Este ejercicio tiene como objetivo poner de manifiesto las habilidades analíticas y de aporte de valor del candidato a las empresas o proyectos a travès del anàlisis de datos. Para este caso se plantea a la empresa Wallmart guiados por el set de datos de la competencia en Kaggle: https://www.kaggle.com/c/walmart-recruiting-store-sales-forecasting/data

#Fecha que representa el valor inferior
min_date=max(train$Date)-31-30-1

data_1=features[(features$Date>=min_date)&(features$Date<=max(train$Date)),]

data_2=train_stores %>%  group_by(Store, Date) %>% summarise(sales = sum(Weekly_Sales), IsHoliday=first(IsHoliday), Type=first(Type), Size=first(Size))

data_2=data_2[(data_2$Date>=min_date)&(data_2$Date<=max(train$Date)),]


data_3 = merge(data_1, data_2)

3. Exploración de Relación de ventas - rebajas promocionales

data_4 %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Total_MarkDown, y=sales)) +
    geom_point(alpha=0.3) +
  geom_label_repel(aes(label = Store), size = 3, max.overlaps=50)

data_4 %>%
    ggplot(aes(x=Total_MarkDown, y=sales, size= Size, color=Type)) +
    geom_point(alpha=0.3) + scale_size(range = c(.1, 10), name="Size")

 data_4 %>%  ggplot(aes(x=Total_MarkDown, y=sales, size= Size, color=IsHoliday)) +
   geom_point(alpha=0.7) + scale_size(range = c(.1, 10), name="Size") +
  geom_label_repel(aes(label = Store), size = 3, max.overlaps=50)

  data_4 %>%  ggplot(aes(x=Total_MarkDown, y=sales, size= Size, color=IsHoliday)) +
   geom_point(alpha=0.7) + scale_size(range = c(.1,10)) + 
  geom_label_repel(aes(label = Store), size = 3, max.overlaps=50) + stat_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y ~ x) + geom_vline(xintercept = mean(data_4$Total_MarkDown)) + geom_hline(yintercept = mean(data_4$sales))

data_6=data_4 %>%  group_by(Store) %>% summarise(Total_MarkDown_Store = sum(Total_MarkDown),sales = sum(sales), IsHoliday=first(IsHoliday), Type=first(Type), Size=first(Size))



data_6 %>%  ggplot(aes(x=Total_MarkDown_Store, y=sales, size= Size, color=IsHoliday)) +
   geom_point(alpha=0.7) + scale_size(range = c(.1,10)) +
  geom_label_repel(aes(label = Store), size = 3, max.overlaps=50) + stat_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y ~ x) + geom_vline(xintercept = mean(data_6$Total_MarkDown_Store)) + geom_hline(yintercept = mean(data_6$sales)) 

data_6 %>%  ggplot(aes(x=Total_MarkDown_Store, y=sales, size= Size, color=IsHoliday)) +
